oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: 1919 Nashville Parade Medal
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: This medal was presented to James McFerren Johnston upon his return after World War I. He participated in the 1919 parade of veterans through Nashville, Tennessee. On the back, the medal is inscribed, "Presented by the citizens of Nashville, Tennessee to their loyal fighting boys." The medal has a star inside of a circle with an eagle on top. The ribbon is vertically striped red, white and blue. Pvt. James McFerren Johnston, HQ Co., Ord. Corps, attached to the 114th MG Battn., 30th Div.
